14:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Elai and Hour One share a solid foundation of core features including Text To Video, Avatar Talking Head, Auto Captions, Templates. Where Elai pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Stock Footage, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Hour One uniquely offers Batch Processing, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Elai holds an overall score of 6/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Hour One scores 6/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
15:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Elai offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $23/mo, compared to Hour One's starting price of $25/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Elai's free tier and Hour One's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
